measurements from adult and juvenile species of the North Pacific.  Otoliths from a variety of species have been measured using digital imaging, calipers, and digital balances. Fish specimens such as walleye pollock, rockfish, sculpins, skates, and forage fish were collected as early as 1990 and otolith measurement data was generated from 2000 to present.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>Otolith measurements were collected for purposes such as confirming species identification, documentation of destroyed structures, and verifying reported fish lengths.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:purpose>          <gmd:status>             <gmd:MD_ProgressCode
